args:
Seimei defeats both Doman and the shikigami
Gozu Tenno and chooses to live with the burden
of the curse. His mission complete, he and
his group start to head back to Hinomoto,
but then return to the Halidom to spread
good fortune for the new year!

No... No! My grand shikigami was wrought
from the amalgamation of Yomi chi and
one of the Great Twelve, and yet you STILL
managed to destroy it?!
Ha ha! Splendid, Seimei. I thought I would\nwould be the one to devour you, and yet\nnow I am the one being devoured.
Should have killed me when you had\nthe chance, Doman. Half-measures\nnever end up well.
O that which shines as the sun!\nI beseech you, purify wickedness!\nBurn it all away!

Aaaaah ha ha ha ha! WONDERFUL!
Today, Seimei, you are the greatest of
onmyoji—and your reward shall be the
greatest of all curses! AAAAH HA HA!
My Kodoku is being made manifest at last!\nYOU are my ultimate sorcery, Seimei!\nYou! Youuu! YOUUU!
I figured a forbidden curse would mean\na lifetime of constant burning and agony,\nbut it barely even tickles.
Aw, I'm just so darn tootin' relieved!
Don't glom onto me, stupid fox.
I'm just so happy, Lord Seimei!\n*sniff* *sniff* Waaaaaah!
You planning to hug me as well?\nBe careful—you're likely to smash\nmy bones to splinters.
No. I only wish to thank you.
All I could imagine was our dying together,\nyet you have opened the way to a future\nwhere we both might live on.
As such, I will endeavor all the more in my\nloyalty to you, Lord Seimei. May ours\ncontinue to be a most fruitful bond.
Laying on the formality a bit thick there,\nGozu Tenno. Still...good on you.
Heck yeah! I love it when everything turns\nout and we all get a happy ending!
Let us not forget that the Halidom\nis back in our hands once more.
Which reminds me, what will happen to\nthat foul miasma that was released?
Not a problem. Once the source is cut off,\nthe mana in the area will purify it.\nMight just take a little time, is all.
Then it really is all over.
Yep! All wrapped up with a nice little bow.

Y'all were just a dilly of a help, so thanks
a heap for that! Still, guess it's time for
this ol' fox to hop on back to Hinomoto and
let folks know what done happened here.
You Wyrmclan folks sure are busy.\nBut when things calm down, feel free\nto come back and visit anytime.
I'm not coming to a place like this again\nunless there is work to be done.
Now hush with that talk, Lord Seimei!\nAin't no problem what for a feller to\ntake a load off once in a tick.
Silence, you stupid fox. I'm not saying\nI won't EVER come here—merely that I\nwouldn't mind if duty brought me this way.
Oooo, I see! Well then, next time you have\nsome work here—and I mean aaaaany\ntiiiiiny thing—feel free to pop around!
Phew, we had a heckuva start to the\nnew year.

Yes, and I fear the Halidom is something
of a wreck after this latest incident. I know
we cleaned up at the end of last year,
but it seems we must do so again.
Easy, Luca. We'll get the place spiffed up\nand then have our New Year's celebration.
And we'll make it DOUBLE humongous to\nmake up for the fact that we won't be\ncelebrating with a Wyrmclan leader!
MUST you make that stupid face?
What the hey's going on?\nDidn't you people just leave yesterday?
I didn't come back because I wanted to.
Ha! Actually, we met with a messenger\nfrom the shogunate yesterday.
He stated that with our mission finished,\nwe should spread good fortune in Alberia.
Just when I thought I was out...
Well, if it means we can celebrate New\nYear's with you all, then I'm thrilled!
We feel the same; it is our honor to\ndeliver both good faith and fortune.
This here's all part'a our duty, Lord Seimei,\nso ya gotta put yer back to that mill wheel\nand push 'er till the work is done!
This coming from the same fox who\nspends all her time on watch goofing off.

I ain't never! I take m'turn on the watch
as seriously as a newborn mare's mama!
...Just like to duck out for the occasional
trip to town is all.
Ha ha! Well, a detour from one's duty is\nplenty welcome here. By all means, please\nhave some fun here in Alberia with us.
I get the feeling this year is going to be\nanother lively one.
(In the end, she never showed up...\nOh well. I'll just have to continue playing\nwith the Mukuroshu.)
(Next time, I WILL have you take\nthe stage...)
